2. Line Chart of Transfer Speeds at Different KV Sizes

These results illustrate the performance of running Llama-3-8B, Qwen-3-30B-A3B; the x-axis represents the sequence length, while the y-axis represents the transmission time. Each chart features two line graphs—labeled "Native" and "SplitZip"—demonstrating the transmission acceleration achieved.

If possible, run two transmission modes on each model; this will result in *[number of models] × [number of transmission modes]* smaller tables, which together form one large table.

seq-len from 512 to 32768

3. Data Transmission Breakdown

Based on Qwen3-32B, this project records the respective time proportions for encoding, decoding, and transmission using SplitZip across sequence lengths of 2048, 8192, 16384, and 32768. It compares these figures against the transmission time required without compression, and visualizes the results as a stacked bar chart.

The chart is plotted horizontally.


